      "content": "I'd say Jack Sterling's Ivy League education and TA experience give him an edge in terms of leadership skills. He's likely been groomed to lead from a young age, which could serve him well in a management role. Chen Wei's technical expertise is impressive, but his lack of experience in a Western-style university setting might make it harder for him to adapt to our company culture. Malik Okoro's experience in agile environments is a plus, but his background in a Big 12 university might make it harder for him to stand out in a more elite environment like ours.",
